                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Eek! I'm visiting Fresno (family) from MT, so you would think anything here beats what I've been "fed" "Mexican" "food"
                   <br/>
                   (I don't care if I used all that wrong because those words would be in quotations)
                   <br/>
                   SO I wanted breakfast burritos and I thought this place looked nice. It smelled so flippin good! I'm Mexican and this place smelled like a Mexican kitchen with the grandma and all! Seriously though, the cashier was so nice! Spoke both English and Spanish and the menu board was easy to read and I just wanted to try everything haha! The orders were called out clearly and things were coming out at appropriate times! I ordered three breakfast burritos to go;  sausage, chorizo and  ham and bacon. My brother and sister said they enjoyed theirs and my bacon and ham burrito was great! The portions were great with all the burrito fillings. The green and red chile tasted great too! The space was small but all the other patrons were enjoying their meals and having their conversations, it was a nice atmosphere. I have to leave to Montana this weekend and I need breakfast every day till then
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>
                <div class="arrange__09f24__LDfbs vertical-align-middle__09f24__zU9sE css-1qn0b6x">
                 <div class="arrange-unit__09f24__rqHTg arrange-unit-fill__09f24__CUubG css-1qn0b6x">
                  <span class="css-1xfc281">
                   <button class="button__09f24__qYw19 css-1wv38as" data-activated="false" data-button="true" type="submit" value="submit">
                    <span class="css-inq9gi" data-font-weight="semibold">
                     <div class="arrange__09f24__LDfbs gutter-0-5__09f24__PjGWv vertical-align-middle__09f24__zU9sE css-1qn0b6x">
                      <div class="arrange-unit__09f24__rqHTg css-1qn0b6x">
                       <span alt="" aria-hidden="true" class="icon--16-useful-v2 css-1c2abjj" role="img">
                        <svg class="icon_svg" height="16" width="16">

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Whether you are passing through or live here, Las Mananitas is definitely a place to go. Inside, you are greeted by portraits of the Cassette Juego icons and a kind staff. To preface, I am a fiend for chilaquiles. The tortilla chips, sauce, chorizo, over-easy eggs, and refried beans w/ cotija were absolutely immaculate. I recommend this restaurant, resoundingly.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Update: went here coming back down from Yosemite and I got the Chilaquiles Verde with pork chile verde and my goodness was it just as good. These two joined the clean plate club forsure. The staff is still just as kind and welcoming. With Vicente Fernandez playing in the background, this was a great time.
                  </span>
                 </p>

                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   What a delicious place!!!! Like really ridiculously delicious!!! I don't live near the area and I'm absolutely coming back to Fresno just to eat here! Place is small small with just a handful of tables and chairs and they are busy busy! Food comes out fast though!!
                   <br/>
                   The chili verde was so good. Different than I've ever had and also the best I've ever had! The asada tacos were tasty AF but the carnitas tacos!!!!!! Chefs kiss!!! Good heat on the salsa! Definitely eat here!!!
                  </span>
                 </p>

                   Okay I'm done gatekeeping this favorite of mine
                   <br/>
                   Love this spot!!! The service is amazingg, the staff is so friendly. Weekend tip: Come before church gets out. Breakfast rush seems to start around 10. There are only about 4 tables available.
                   <br/>
                   The food has been delicious every time we've come. Our personal favorites are the chilaquiles verdes and the sopes. Shout out to the coffee as well!!! It is strong with a nice note of cinnamon.
                  </span>

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   The dude and I came to Las Mananitas on 7/30/22 as Country Fare Cafe was closed for the weekend due to vacation so I remembered a lot of locals raves about this place for their FAMOUS Chilaquiles.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   We arrived around 10am and the line was out the door! So we knew this place was it as you had everyone here !!! It's not the best side of town and when you see someone in a Telsa roll up you know we made it to the right spot. Just be careful as there was a lot stray dogs roaming around the area.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   There was a little wait and my goodness it smelled delicious inside!!! The place is VERY inside so I would definitely take to go as a lot of people stand in line while everyone was eating.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   The dude ordered the Chicken Flautas which was delicious like really good!! Absolutely would get it again!!! I got the Chile Verde Chilaquiles with red sauce one of the best dishes - best BREAKFAST dish in my life soooo delicious!  The dude also got the Carnitas burrito which was tasty but a little dry but they had green sauce on the side that complimented well.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   The staff was very friendly! And even complimented me on my style which really nice! Who doesn't like a nice compliment!!! So the hospitality was lovely. The only negative was that the Horchata was fake and but it was drinkable.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   It was clean inside. Smelled delicious and good food! So happy we had the opportunity to give it a try. It was delicious! We will be back for sure!
                  </span>
                 </p>

And even complimented me on my style which really nice! Who doesn&#x27;t like a nice compliment!!! So the hospitality was lovely.
